  "schema_name": "eywa_node_response",
  "schema_version": "v1",
  "orchestration_decision": "delegate",
  "decision_notes": "The problem asks for the minimum Hamming weight of the product 2023 * n. Since n can be any positive integer, this is equivalent to finding the minimum number of ones in the binary representation of any multiple of 2023. This is a problem of finding the smallest weight of a multiple of a given integer, which relates to the properties of the number in base 2.",
  "helpers": [
    {
      "label": "helper_1",
      "instructions": "Analyze the number 2023 in binary. Determine if there exists an n such that 2023 * n is a power of 2. If not, prove why 2023 is not a divisor of any power of 2 by examining its prime factorization. This establishes whether k(n) = 1 is possible."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_2",
      "instructions": "Investigate if k(n) = 2 is possible. This is equivalent to checking if there exist integers a and b (where a > b >= 0) such that 2023 divides (2^a + 2^b). This can be simplified to checking if 2023 divides 2^b * (2^(a-b) + 1), which reduces to checking if 2023 divides 2^m + 1 for some m. Test small values of m or use modular arithmetic (specifically looking at the order of 2 modulo the odd factors of 2023) to determine if such an m exists."
    },
    {
      "label": "helper_3",
      "instructions": "If k(n) = 2 is not possible, investigate if k(n) = 3 is possible. This requires checking if 2023 divides 2^a + 2^b + 2^c for some a > b > c >= 0. This is equivalent to checking if 2023 divides 2^c * (2^(a-c) + 2^(b-c) + 1), which reduces to checking if 2023 divides 2^x + 2^y + 1 for some x > y > 0. Use modular arithmetic to test the existence of such x and y."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent agent will take the results from the helpers sequentially. First, confirm if k(n)=1 is impossible. Second, if k(n)=1 is impossible, check if k(n)=2 is possible. If k(n)=2 is impossible, check if k(n)=3 is possible. The first k(n) value that is proven to be possible is the final answer."
}

